title: Not Your Everyday Kinghunt || Cori vs Firouzja || PRO Chess League (2020)

Jorge Cori vs Alireza Firouzja
ProChess League
12.3.2020.
Queen's Gambit Declined, Marshall defence (D06)

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. c4 e6 4. e3 Be7 5. Nc3 O-O 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bd3 c6 8. h3 Re8 9. Qc2 Bd6 10. Bd2 Nbd7 11. g4 Qe7 12. O-O-O Ne4 13. Rdf1 Nf8 14. Kb1 Ng6 15. Bc1 Bb4 16. Ne2 Bd7 17. Nf4 Rac8 18. Nxg6 hxg6 19. Ne5 c5 20. Qe2 c4 21. Bxe4 dxe4 22. f4 c3 23. f5 Ba4 24. fxg6 f6 25. g5 cxb2 26. Bxb2 Rc2 27. Qh5 Rxb2+ 28. Kxb2 Bc3+ 29. Kxc3 Rc8+ 30. Nc4 Rxc4+ 31. Kxc4 b5+ 32. Kc3 Qa3+ 33. Kd2 Qd3+ 34. Ke1 Qxe3+ 35. Qe2 Qg3+ 36. Kd2 Qxg5+ 37. Qe3 Qd5 38. Rc1 Qxa2+ 39. Ke1

1. Each team has a roster of 8 to 16 players. 4 of these players will be chosen to compete in each league match.
2. Each team can have no more than 5 players rated above 2700 on their roster.
3. Each team can have no more than 10 players rated above 2600 on their roster.
4. The PRO Chess Season uses the most recent December FIDE Rating List.
5. You can add a player to your roster at any time during the season.
​6. You may add more than 16 players, however every extra player above 16 will cost your team a half point in the standings.

Read more here https://www.prochessleague.com/rules-new.html
